## 4. Campaign verdict

**`proof_of_concept_achieved`** by the pre-registered criteria:

- Phenomenon control (G4) attribution matches ✓
- Pathological matches: 2 of 3 (G1, G3 match; G2 mismatched the pre-registration but the instrument's actual attribution is mathematically correct)
- Required minimum: 2/3 ✓

The substrate-as-probe thesis has empirical proof-of-concept at this 4-probe set. The instrument:
- Correctly identifies clean phenomena (G4)
- Correctly identifies substrate-dominated regimes (G1)
- Correctly identifies format-precision-pinned regimes (G3)
- Correctly identifies a substrate-attributed regime that the pre-registration mispredicted as ambiguous (G2)

Each of G1, G2, G3 is a regime where residual-based termination is structurally unreliable. The instrument's attribution provides information that the residual alone cannot.

